# 🌐 Networking Theory

# DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)

DHCP automatically assigns IP addresses to devices joining a network.

Without DHCP, every device would require manual IP configuration.

---

# DHCP DORA Process

## D – Discover

The client broadcasts a request asking if any DHCP server is available.

---

## O – Offer

The DHCP server responds by offering an available IP address.

---

## R – Request

The client requests to use the offered IP address.

---

## A – Acknowledge

The DHCP server confirms the assignment and provides network configuration such as:

- IP Address
- Subnet Mask
- Default Gateway
- DNS Server

This completes the DHCP process.

