# Real World Scenario

## Situation

A marketing employee reports:

> "Whenever I try to save my report, I receive a 'Permission Denied' error."

Instead of immediately changing permissions, the administrator investigates.

First, the administrator checks file ownership.

```bash
ls -l
```

The administrator discovers that the file belongs to another user.

After confirming ownership requirements, the administrator updates the ownership appropriately.

The employee successfully saves the report.

This prevents unnecessary permission changes while maintaining system security.

